.TH OPENTELEMETRY-DOTNET 8 "@DATE@" "opentelemetry-dotnet-autoinstrumentation @VERSION@" "System Administration"
.SH NAME
opentelemetry-dotnet \- OpenTelemetry .NET Auto-Instrumentation
.SH SYNOPSIS
The .NET instrumentation is loaded automatically by the OpenTelemetry Injector
when a .NET application starts.
.SH DESCRIPTION
The OpenTelemetry .NET Auto-Instrumentation automatically instruments
.NET applications to collect distributed traces, metrics, and logs without
requiring code changes.
.PP
When used with the OpenTelemetry Injector package, the agent is automatically
attached to all .NET processes. The injector resolves the agent path as
<prefix>/<libc>; this package bundles the glibc variant only, since musl-based
distributions (Alpine Linux) use apk packages, which this project does not
build.
.SH FILES
.TP
.B /usr/lib/opentelemetry/dotnet/glibc/
Directory containing the managed assemblies and the native profiler library
(glibc variant) for .NET instrumentation.
.TP
.B /etc/opentelemetry/dotnet/otel-config.yaml
Optional declarative configuration file.
.TP
.B /etc/opentelemetry/injector/conf.d/dotnet.conf
Drop-in configuration file that registers the .NET agent path prefix with
the injector.
.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
.B OTEL_SERVICE_NAME
Set the service name for telemetry data.
.TP
.B OTEL_EXPORTER_OTLP_ENDPOINT
Set the OTLP exporter endpoint (e.g., http://localhost:4317).
.TP
.B OTEL_TRACES_EXPORTER
Set the traces exporter (otlp, console, none). Default: otlp
.TP
.B OTEL_METRICS_EXPORTER
Set the metrics exporter (otlp, console, none). Default: otlp
.TP
.B OTEL_LOGS_EXPORTER
Set the logs exporter (otlp, console, none). Default: otlp
.TP
.B OTEL_DOTNET_AUTO_INSTRUMENTATION_ENABLED
Set to "false" to disable. Default: true
.TP
.B OTEL_EXPERIMENTAL_FILE_BASED_CONFIGURATION_ENABLED
Set to "true" to enable declarative configuration. Default: false
.TP
.B OTEL_CONFIG_FILE
Path to a declarative configuration file.
.SH NOTES
The bundle installs under a glibc/ subdirectory, matching the injector's
<prefix>/<libc> resolution scheme. Only the glibc variant is bundled: musl-based
distributions (Alpine Linux) use apk packages, which this project does not
build.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR opentelemetry-injector (8),
.BR dotnet (1)
.PP
